1
00:00:10,250 --> 00:00:11,500
On average,

2
00:00:12,450 --> 00:00:14,290
a person encounters
1,000 people per day.

3
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:22,200
Which amounts to

4
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:24,790
29.2 million people
in a lifetime.

5
00:00:30,450 --> 00:00:32,660
The probability of
two people meeting

6
00:00:32,660 --> 00:00:34,410
is 4 in 100,000.

7
00:00:41,950 --> 00:00:44,160
The probability of
getting to know each other

8
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:46,080
is 5 in 10 million.

9
00:00:50,580 --> 00:00:52,250
And the probability of
falling in love

10
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,620
is only 1 in 1.5 billion.

11
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,790
Liking someone

12
00:01:05,790 --> 00:01:08,120
is a rare occurrence.

13
00:01:11,580 --> 00:01:12,620
So,

14
00:01:14,410 --> 00:01:16,790
when you meet someone who
resonates with you on the same frequency,

15
00:01:21,330 --> 00:01:23,580
it's an incredible
stroke of luck.

16
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,200
But that kind of luck

17
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:51,250
depends on perfect timing.

18
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:52,040
Cut.

19
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,580
This is a dating show.

20
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:59,870
Everyone signed up
to find love.

21
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:02,250
So what's so lucky
about that?

22
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:08,250
Meeting on this show
is its own kind of luck.

23
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:12,410
I told you,

24
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:16,250
this show is about
taking charge of love.

25
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,330
I'll revise it later.

26
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:20,040
Your turn,

27
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:20,700
Henry.

28
00:02:22,450 --> 00:02:26,120
We've gotten
46 applications so far.

29
00:02:26,450 --> 00:02:28,370
First up, the sweet guy.

30
00:02:28,370 --> 00:02:30,290
He's warm, friendly,

31
00:02:30,290 --> 00:02:31,200
and adorable.

32
00:02:31,450 --> 00:02:32,500
He plays guitar too.

33
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,410
Next.

34
00:02:35,580 --> 00:02:38,370
Okay, the second type
is the "bat" boy.

35
00:02:38,370 --> 00:02:40,540
He's hot, cool,

36
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:42,120
and says
whatever's on his mind.

37
00:02:43,290 --> 00:02:44,290
"Bat" boy?

38
00:02:44,950 --> 00:02:45,830
What's that?

39
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:50,790
A sexy boy.

40
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:56,040
Okay.

41
00:02:57,120 --> 00:03:00,540
Okay. Next up,
the class clown.

42
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:02,120
He's a total dork.

43
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:05,580
Funny,
always joking around.

44
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:10,160
Are we really
putting people in boxes?

45
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:13,410
You like labeling people
that much?

46
00:03:13,790 --> 00:03:15,000
Then what would you be?

47
00:03:15,950 --> 00:03:16,790
Short and feisty?

48
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:19,160
I'm just trying
to brainstorm.

49
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,120
How many ideas
have you got?

50
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,500
Let's see...

51
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:24,830
Five.

52
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:27,080
Come back after fifty.

53
00:03:30,540 --> 00:03:33,080
Lisa, I've got one.

54
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:34,830
This is January.

55
00:03:34,830 --> 00:03:37,700
She was one of YouTube's
first big influencers.

56
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,700
Her popularity's
slowed down,

57
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,700
but she's still
well known.

58
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,330
Still has a fanbase.
Keep her.

59
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,290
Next is Phil.

60
00:03:47,290 --> 00:03:49,080
He first got noticed
during lockdown.

61
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:52,700
He's an influencer
and singer.

62
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,120
He blew up recently

63
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,790
after his friends

64
00:03:55,790 --> 00:03:57,290
Clare and Lucas broke up.

65
00:03:57,290 --> 00:03:59,120
He went after Lucas,

66
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,330
and the clip went viral.

67
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:03,000
I'm not letting go.

68
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,870
Hey! Let go!

69
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:06,080
You're the cheater here.

70
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:08,660
And you're making her
play the happy couple?

71
00:04:08,660 --> 00:04:09,790
What kind of man are you?

72
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:11,000
Own what you did.

73
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,790
Mind your own business!

74
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,120
Clare is my business.

75
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,910
He could work.

76
00:04:15,910 --> 00:04:18,580
Have you reached out
to his manager or agency?

77
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:20,620
Yeah, but we haven't
heard back yet.

78
00:04:21,870 --> 00:04:23,000
Cole,

79
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,620
he graduated from BYC too.
Know him?

80
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:34,000
I doubt he'll come.

81
00:04:34,620 --> 00:04:36,830
I don't care how you do it.

82
00:04:36,830 --> 00:04:39,120
I want both of them here
by next week.

83
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:08,250
It's been a while.

84
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:21,870
Remember me?

85
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,330
Which one
do you like better?

86
00:05:39,330 --> 00:05:40,040
This one or this one?

87
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,040
(Elevator doors closing)

88
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,200
They're about the same.

89
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,580
About the same?

90
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:52,950
(Elevator doors closing)

91
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,450
Hi, Phil.

92
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:02,950
I'm Candy.

93
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,790
I reached out to you,

94
00:06:04,790 --> 00:06:07,290
but I guess
you missed my email.

95
00:06:07,290 --> 00:06:09,120
No worries, though.

96
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,450
Cole knows you.

97
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:18,910
He's pretty handsome
in person!

98
00:06:22,370 --> 00:06:24,450
The show's called
Love Algorithm.

99
00:06:24,450 --> 00:06:27,000
Three guys and three women
live together

100
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,580
and try to find a match.

101
00:06:32,370 --> 00:06:33,950
Life's too short.

102
00:06:33,950 --> 00:06:36,580
So go after what you want.

103
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:40,080
Especially when it
comes to love.

104
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:44,120
You wrote that?

105
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:53,080
Your dating show's
gonna be a blast.

106
00:06:54,660 --> 00:06:56,370
With Cole,

107
00:06:56,370 --> 00:06:59,120
there's always drama

108
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,870
and messy relationships.

109
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,540
Right?

110
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:08,790
Let's take a break.

111
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,120
Alright.

112
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:39,000
Hey, give it back.

113
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:42,540
Seriously?

114
00:07:42,910 --> 00:07:43,910
Not even one sip?

115
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:45,200
Nope.

116
00:07:48,290 --> 00:07:49,540
Thanks.

117
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,040
You drank the whole thing!

118
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:55,540
Hey,

119
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:57,080
Yaowei! Wenhan!

120
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:57,830
Jing Tong?

121
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:58,910
Get over here
and help me!

122
00:07:58,910 --> 00:07:59,790
I got you.

123
00:07:59,790 --> 00:08:01,000
I'll help you too.

124
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:42,870
Looks like you're
doing well here.

125
00:08:46,330 --> 00:08:48,290
Are you really
gonna do it?

126
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:53,040
Do you want me to?

127
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:02,870
Can we stick to business?

128
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:20,700
This is business.

129
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:29,330
You can't even
button your own shirt?

130
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:34,540
Chin up.

131
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:41,120
So, are you taking
Jing Tong to the prom?

132
00:09:41,830 --> 00:09:44,000
You gonna ask her?

133
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:45,450
No.

134
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:48,500
Then

135
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:51,250
neither of us
goes with anyone.

136
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:52,330
Fair,

137
00:09:53,910 --> 00:09:54,910
yeah?

138
00:09:56,290 --> 00:09:57,080
Yeah.

139
00:10:00,290 --> 00:10:01,120
And this.

140
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,290
What's this?

141
00:10:04,410 --> 00:10:07,790
Our band outfits.

142
00:10:07,790 --> 00:10:08,750
You wear one,

143
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:11,830
I'll wear the other.

144
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,000
Here?

145
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:20,910
Picture us up on stage.

146
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:23,700
Shining...

147
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:29,000
Sparkly, sparkly!

148
00:10:29,580 --> 00:10:32,500
Sparkly, sparkly! Haha!

149
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:51,540
I'm not doing your show.

